zed debt obligation vehicle ares would grow to manage a family of collateralized loan obligation clo vehicles that would invest in capital marketsbased securities including senior bank loans and highyield and mezzanine debt ares was founded by antony ressler and john h kissick both partners at apollo as well as bennett rosenthal who joined the group from the global leveraged finance group at merrill lynch ares i and ii which were raised were structured as market value clos ares iii though ares x were structured as cash flow clos in  ares completed a spinout from apollo management although technically the founders of ares had completed a spinout with the formation of the firm in  they had maintained a close relationship with apollo over its first five years and operated as the west coast affiliate of apollo shortly thereafter ares completed fundraising for ares corporate opportunities fund a special situations investment fund with 0 million of capital under management in  ares debuted a publicly traded business development company ares capital corporation nasdaqarcc in  ares raised a  billion successor special situations fund ares corporate opportunities fund ii referencesedit  httpiragmcomphoenixzhtmlc0pirolnewsarticleid0  apollo global management form 0q for the quarterly period ended march  0 secgov retrieved june  0   leon d black business week snapshot  mittelman melissa  october 0 apollo to raise new lbo fund as it spends more than ever before bloomberg news bloomberg lp retrieved  november 0   deal maker’s day tally  billion new york times   drexel divided on settlement new york times december    a b exdrexel executives arrange aid for fruit of the loom august    changes at drexel continue new york times march    drexels uncertain future new york times october    bailing out frances biggest bank new york times january    altman edward i the high yield bond market a decade of assessment comparing  with 0 nyu stern school of business 0  hylton richard d corporat